; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures SCU CLK and generates a certain frequency of Main Clock.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Make an environment to measure clock frequency by clock output port.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. SCUCLK
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. CLKO    : PB2 (Clock Output)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; PCU (PF4)
; 1. Port                      : [ 1 2 a 3 ]
;    Port Group Number         : 1 (B group)
;    Pin Number                : 2
;    Pin Mode                  : Alternative (Mux)
;    Pin Alt Number            : 3
;
; SCUCLK
; 1. Clkout                    : [ m 0 e ]
;    Clock Source              : m (MCLK : Main Clock)
;    Clock Source Divide       : 2
;    Clock Output Enable       : e (Enable)
;
; 2. MCLK                      : [ e 0 ]
;    Clock Source              : e (HSI : High Speed Internal Oscillator)
;    Clock Source Divide       : 0
;
; SCUCLK
sendln 'cm scuclk'
mpause 30
sendln 'clkout m 2 e'
mpause 30
sendln 'mclk h 0'
